              <div class="content__page-desc">
                <h3>Countertop Microwave Ovens</h3>
                <p>
                  Countertop microwave ovens are the most common type and are
                  generally more affordable and easier to install. However, they
                  are also prone to a variety of repair needs. One frequent
                  issue is a faulty door switch, which can prevent the microwave
                  from heating food. If your microwave isn't working properly, a
                  qualified technician may need to replace the door switch.
                  Water or insect infestation can also disrupt the electronics,
                  requiring a thorough cleaning or replacement of affected
                  components. The turntable's turning mechanism can also fail,
                  which may necessitate the replacement of the motor or belt.
                  Issues with the high voltage diode or capacitor can prevent
                  the microwave from powering on, requiring specialized testing
                  and repair.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="content__page-desc">
                <h3>Built-in Microwave Ovens</h3>
                <p>
                  Built-in microwave ovens offer a sleek, integrated look but
                  come with their own set of challenges. Repairing these units
                  often requires more expertise due to their complex
                  installation. A broken microwave door can be particularly
                  problematic as it usually involves more intricate components
                  compared to countertop models. Faulty door switches are still
                  a common issue, but accessing them can be more difficult.
                  Control panel failures are another frequent problem, often
                  requiring the replacement of the entire panel by a qualified
                  technician. Additionally, built-in microwaves are more
                  susceptible to defective magnetrons, which may need to be
                  replaced if the unit stops heating food effectively.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="content__page-desc">
                <h3>Over-the-Range Microwave Ovens</h3>
                <p>
                  Over-the-range microwave ovens combine microwave cooking with
                  a range hood, making them multifunctional but also more
                  complex to repair. They often suffer from the same door switch
                  issues as other types but may also experience problems with
                  the ventilation system. A defective magnetron or high voltage
                  diode can render the microwave useless, necessitating expert
                  advice for a proper fix. The control panel can also fail,
                  requiring a replacement part to restore functionality. Given
                  their placement, these microwaves are also more prone to
                  insect infestation, which can affect the electronics and
                  require a thorough cleaning and inspection.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="content__page-desc">
                <h3>Drawer Microwave Ovens</h3>
                <p>
                  Drawer microwave ovens are becoming increasingly popular for
                  their convenience and modern design. However, their unique
                  construction can lead to specific repair challenges. The
                  turning mechanism, often a stirrer belt in these models, can
                  malfunction, affecting the microwave's ability to heat food
                  evenly. The control panel is also a common point of failure
                  and may need to be replaced to get the unit working properly.
                  Door switches and the high voltage diode are other components
                  that frequently require attention. Given the specialized
                  nature of these microwaves, repairs often come at a higher
                  cost and should be handled by a qualified technician.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="content__page-desc">
                <h3>Commercial Microwave Ovens</h3>
